<item>
            <title>[PDFBOX-3250] Possible errors in TrueType table &apos;name&apos; parsing.</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/PDFBOX-3250</link>
                <project id="12310760" key="PDFBOX">PDFBox</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Accidentally noticed a possible bug in parsing name records:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;1) Class NamingTable.java, line 165:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;for (int i = 4; i &amp;lt;= 0; i--)&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;this loop is never entered, thus, Unicode strings are not considered.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;2) Class NamingTable.java, line 106:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;String string = data.readString(nr.getStringLength(), charset);&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;for platform == 0 (Unicode), strings are read in ISO-8859-1 charset, but most likely it should be UTF16 charset.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;This may affect values of the FontFamily and FontSubFamily fields.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment>Unicode strings</environment>
